    • Method Detail

      • matches

        public boolean matches(de.unkrig.lfr.core.MatcherImpl matcher)
        Checks whether this sequence matches the subject of the matcher, starting at the current MatcherImpl.offset.

        If this sequence matches, then the method advances the MatcherImpl.offset to the offset of the first character after the match, replaces the MatcherImpl.groups with an array that reflects the groups after the matching, and returns true.

        Otherwise, if this sequence does not match, then the MatcherImpl.groups remain unchanged, the MatcherImpl.offset is undefined, and the method returns false.

        In both cases, MatcherImpl.hitEnd is set to true iff an attempt was made to peek past the matcher's region.

        See Also:
        Matcher.region(int, int), MatcherImpl.groups, MatcherImpl.hitEnd

      • find

        public int find(de.unkrig.lfr.core.MatcherImpl matcher)
        Searches for the next match, starting at the current MatcherImpl.offset, and, iff it finds one, updates MatcherImpl.offset to point behind the match, and returns the index of the start of the match.

        Derived classes may override this method if there is a faster implementation.

        Returns:
        -1 iff there is no match
